To create instance of FSM, a helper method Fsm is provided as shown in example. This method takes following parameters:
name of FSM for logging initial state of the FSM block having states of the FSM
Kotlin val irisFsm = Fsm(name = "iris-fsm", initState = "INIT") {
    // place to define different states of FSM
}

For creating fsm, the third parameter is a block which is the place to define all the states. A method named state needs to be called with parameters name of the state and the block of actions to be performed when transitioned to that state. When multiple states with same name are added, the last defined state will considered and others will be discarded.
Kotlin state("INIT") {
    // actions to be performed in this state
}
Note State names are case insensitive.

This endpoint allows to submit sequence to sequencer. Sequencer will start executing sequence. This api gives SubmitResponse future as response. Submit won’t wait for final response. It will give started response saying sequence is submitted successfully and started.
Submit POST http://localhost:57542/post-endpoint
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Submit": [
    {
      "Setup": {
        "source": "esw.test",
        "commandName": "command-1",
        "maybeObsId": [],
        "paramSet": []
      }
    },
    {
      "Setup": {
        "source": "esw.test",
        "commandName": "command-2",
        "maybeObsId": [],
        "paramSet": []
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 200 OK HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Server: akka-http/10.1.11
Date: Thu, 02 Jan 2020 06:36:10 GMT
Content-Type: application/json
Content-Length: 60

{
  "Started": {
    "runId": "eee70d8c-8edb-4858-8994-5fe0357d3a90"
  }
}

